@scholzhannah Perhaps we could change both the file locations and the names? (But I'm not very familiar with the folder/namespace structure of mathlib; Someone more experienced than I should leave a comment.)

Currently, the same word (CW-complex) with different modifiers (`Classical` vs `Abstract`, or `Topology.` vs `CategoryTheory.`) is used to refer to the definition in this PR as well as the one in #12502. I am not aware of this practice in the mathematical literature.

I would suggest using two different words, namely "CW-decomposition" and "CW-complex", to distinguish between these two definitions. We could also use "Whitehead complex" and "CW complex". These terminologies are used in the literature, as mentioned above.

